# draft/dsl/ Index

DSL & YAML contracts, shared grammar, manifest wiring, circuit syntax, and playbook documentation.

## Execution order

```
manifest-as-map (Origami)     dsl-lexicon (Asterisk)
        │                           │
        ▼                           ▼
   dsl-wiring (Asterisk, depends on manifest-as-map)
        │
        ├──▶ circuit-dsl-shorthand (depends on dsl-wiring W6)
        └──▶ yaml-playbook-docs (parallel, no dependency)
```

- **manifest-as-map** (Origami `draft/`) provides the `assets:` manifest schema. Must land before dsl-wiring Phase 1.
- **dsl-lexicon** and **manifest-as-map** can run in parallel (no mutual dependency). dsl-lexicon P3.1 deferred until manifest-as-map P4 settles directory structure.
- **dsl-wiring** depends on manifest-as-map for `assets:` schema. Owns component/binding resolution, prompt-on-node, naming conventions.
- **circuit-dsl-shorthand** depends on dsl-wiring W6 (family/transformer unification) for implicit-family logic.
- **yaml-playbook-docs** has no code dependency; can run any time after the DSL shape stabilizes.

## Files
- `dsl-lexicon.md` — Standardized DSL lexicon: `kind:`/`version:` envelope on all YAML files, `references:` FK syntax, artifact schema dedup, vocabulary enums, heuristics naming, dataset externalization. **Gate.**
- `dsl-wiring.md` — Component/binding resolution, prompt-on-node, scorecard-on-circuit, naming conventions (11 open gaps). Cross-repo (Origami + Asterisk). **Gate.** (Renamed from `yaml-cohesion`.)
- `circuit-dsl-shorthand.md` — Cohesive node-scoped edges, auto-inferred topology flags, implicit defaults for circuit YAMLs. **Quick-win.**
- `yaml-playbook-docs.md` — Extend autodoc-generated skeleton with Asterisk narrative, Ansible analogy, project identity. **Quick-win.**
